.SS GET_DIMENSIONS ACTION
.PP
The
.B get_dimensions
action retrieves important screen parameters including screen
dimensions and
.B pwb
output specifications.
The dimension values will be returned in
.B PWB_ASSOC
unless the
.B -A
option is used.
.PP
.pt_get_dimensions
.RS
.TP
.RI [ handle ]
Optional name of handle from which the dimensions are to be retrieved.
If
.I handle
is provided, all of the following array indexes will be set.  Otherwise,
only
.BR screen_lines " and " screen_cols
will be set.
.TP
.BI -A " associative_array_name"
Name of a associative array in which the dimensions should be
returned.
The array will be created if it doesn't already exist.
.IP
If
.B -A
is not used, the dimensions will be returned in
.BR PWB_ASSOC .
.RS
.PP
The index names of the associative array are:
.TS
tab(|);
lb l.
screen_lines|full count of screen lines
screen_cols|full count of screen columns

T{
\ \ \if
.I handle
provided:
T}
data_rows|number of elements in data source
pager_lines|lines controlled by the pager
pager_cols|characters per pager-controlled line
margin_top|number of rows in head (top of screen)
margin_bottom|number of rows in foot (bottom of screen)
margin_left|empty columns left of the content
margin_right|empty columns right of the content
row_top|data row number of top line being displayed
row_focus|data row number that currently has focus
